Marcus Aurelius believed that building time into each day for reflection was essential for peace of mind. Do you give yourself time to reflect. What do you notice if you don\'92t.\
\
\pard\tx0\tx0\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 If I don\'92t reflect I don\'92t appreciate my own achievements, it is like they never existed and put out of my mind. I am not reminded of why/what I do it all for. Yet feel also like I made done anything and am a waste with no direction or reason to be flourishing by using energy for nothing. Like leaving a light on. No gratitude leads to seeking gratification and indulging in excess, as a friendly distraction from the pointlessness that is not lasting or fulfilling and feels wrong or sick. Focus on the mundane compulsory tasks makes me feel resentful for being controlled by what is out of my control. I have no sense of duty or nobility for effort tied to a greater purpose. Fate is pushing me, I am not flowing with it..\
\
